So when it comes to how you can make a real impact, whether it be reducing waste, whether it be finding defects, whether it be you're noticing trends in the manufacturing process that over time that are drifting in the wrong way so you can make corrective action,

00:25:38.439 --> 00:25:49.439
all that requires quick and easy visual access to data as well as the smart analytics to go on top of that to help you get alerts and to know when things are going the wrong way.

00:25:49.439 --> 00:26:04.439
And so one of the things that Catalina and others, other really brilliant data scientists on the team have done is they've used POSIT as the base platform to build a continuous process verification tool.

00:26:04.439 --> 00:26:07.439
Okay, and it actually has multiple facets to it.

00:26:08.439 --> 00:26:14.439
So there's different modules to help you go through the entire process of, okay, I have all this data that's been ingested.

00:26:14.439 --> 00:26:22.439
Now, how do I set control limits that make sense for this particular control metric of this product.

00:26:22.439 --> 00:26:31.439
So I'm measuring this, whether it be percent dissolution or some kind of quality metric that happens at the end of the manufacturing process and that product and that site.

00:26:31.439 --> 00:26:34.439
So for that particular combination.

00:26:34.439 --> 00:26:43.439
What's the historical data look like and what are the control limits that I want to set and there's all kinds of rules, all the, you know, the shoe heart control chart rules.

00:26:44.439 --> 00:26:50.439
What's it called, something Bell, electric bell. What was it, Kelly? I can't remember all the names of the eight roles there you can select from.

00:26:50.439 --> 00:26:57.439
And so there's a module to then select the control chart limits.

00:26:57.439 --> 00:27:05.439
And that'll only be given to a few, the access that will be given to a few of our manufacturing colleagues because that's pretty powerful to be able to set those control limits.

00:27:06.439 --> 00:27:14.439
And then there's the more general module will be to have the continuous monitoring of those and another module that allows you to go in and actually make annotations.

00:27:14.439 --> 00:27:21.439
So you can type in, okay, this particular data point is, you know, out of spec. Here's the reason why. And so that gets tracked.

00:27:21.439 --> 00:27:28.439
Anyone can go back and see that of why it went out of control and as well as things like email alerting.

00:27:28.439 --> 00:27:39.439
Okay. So your process is, is drifting out of control and hit the hit control limit. Now you'll get an email alert right to your inbox. And so then you can quickly go and investigate.

