So, a small and mighty team. I'm really dedicated to help make a difference using data and analytics in our commercial space. And I learned a lot from that. I mean, I learned a lot from mistakes and actual successes. So, let me tell you some of my mistakes, and then maybe that'll help guide you. And I've tried to learn from those mistakes as I've built this new team here at Zoetis.

00:34:22.439 --> 00:34:46.439
So, one of our first mistakes was to try to tackle too many things at once. And so, you know, part of it is like, okay, this is a really powerful capability. We want to make a big difference. So, let's try to go as many places as we can. Now, there's some value to trying to, if you don't really know where the value is, you may kind of try to do quick proof of concepts in many places and whatever one is successful, then you focus on that.

00:34:47.439 --> 00:35:07.439
But I think we just spent too much time trying to work on some inherited projects that we got instead of really trying to focus on where's the real biggest impact going to be. It took us about two years to get to the point where we're like, okay, we found an area that can really make a difference.

00:35:08.439 --> 00:35:25.439
And then by the fourth year, that's when things started to really happen for us. And that's when we narrowed our focus, and we honed in, like put all of our efforts on just a couple things. We're a small team, we can only take on so much. Just focus on one or two things and just really do well at that.

